cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Linear Logic and its use in characterizing complexity classes. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the polynomial time function class FP(K) and its relationship to the BSS model of computation. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper introduces an extension of Terui's lambda calculus. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a possible category as the paper deals with complexity classes and their characterization. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with computation over an arbitrary ring in the BSS model.
